<Author>tywhitney
<Content>Best Hotel Manager Ever Upon arriving in Amsterdam, we were very disoriented. We gladly came to find that the hotel that we had booked was not that far away from centraal station and that it was on a very beautiful and popular road in the city. The hotel itself is situated in a beautiful 150 year old building and our room had a great view of Amsterdam out the window. Rudy is the name of the owner/ manager and he is very very friendly. Just a note, the hotel does not have an elevator and the stairs to navigate the place are pretty intense. Once you get past that, the the view, location and price make up for the lack of room amenities and the climb. There is no T.V. or radio, but like I said, the location is worth it along with the fact that Rudy didn't mind us smoking in the room. I recommend staying in room 7 which is a double room and has a shower and a window that is great for people watching and smoking out of. Let me say again that Rudy the owner is awesome. He discounted our room when we decided to stay there for a second go around, and he gave us our favorite room again. All in all this was a great place for a budget travelor to stay and perfect for two young travelers making there way through the bike madness of Amsterdam. 
