<Author>Waddler
<Content>Cheap, good location - functional Hotels in Amsterdam are expensive - you have got to deal with it, with that in mind this place is very, very good value. We paid 80 Euros for a 4 bed en-suite. We were over for a sports tournament, and weren't going to be hanging around too much so it suited our needs well.I didn't find our room particularly cramped, though it isn't big, and the beds are fairly narrow (I fell out of it one night! But it isn't too high off the floor so it didn't matter!) and the room and en-suite shower/toilet are clean. The location is very central for everything with a tram stop very close that goes up to Central Station, Spui, Leidseplein (all within walkin distance anyway) and the Museumplein, and only a couple of minutes walk from Dam Square. It is also, though on a fairly busy road, very close to one of the prettier canal areas in Amsterdam - just walk up or down Prinsengracht, Keizergracht or Herengracht and the street between them and you'll find traditional homes, boutique shops, canal-side cafes and little bars and restaurants - you are also very close to the atmospheric local Jordaan area.That said, it isn't luxury, there is no breakfast, the stairs are very steep by international standards and there is no other way up (but by no means very steep by Amsterdam standards), there isn't anything in the way of facilities but none of this botheres me.The dude behind the desk was a little odd (he'd gone rifling though my bag because my phone was ringing whilst I was out - which I wasn't too keen on).Seemed quite an international bunch staying there - only 4 or 5 rooms I think. 
