<Content>Good budget option in Amsterdam This is a superbly located small backpacker type hotel just a couple of minutes walk from Dam square. It was very basic (with the double bed being closer to 3 quarter size and the room being smaller than anything else we stayed in in Europe) but clean and tidy, which was exactly what we wanted after getting of the plane after a 12 hour flight. The steep stairs were not a problem for us but I can see how they could be for someone older or with heavy suitcases (we had packs). The shared shower was clean and always free when we wanted it but was literally located in a cupboard in the hallway. The price seemed a little steep for such basic accommodation at 60 euros per night (plus 5% tax - a hidden cost), especially compared with lovely renovated hotels we stayed at in places like Paris and Bordeaux however I agree that it is excellent for Amsterdam - most places are in need of renovation and bedrooms are uniformly tiny. The owner was very helpful and gave good advice and service.Whilst something bigger, newer and cheaper would have been great, I would still stay here again as I know that Amsterdam is small, old and expensive, and the excellent location makes this hotel stand out amongst a mediocre bunch. 
