<Content>Perfect location, great price I stayed in a single at the Hotel Aspen for 5 nights in early April. It fulfilled all of my requirements for a hotel: clean, comfortable bed, convenient location, and good price. At the Aspen, you get the added bonus of Esam, the proprietor, who is always willing to offer restaurant and transportation suggestions as well as the weather forecast, maps, and umbrellas. Quite the character! The hotel is walking distance to Centraal Station and all of the major sights. My room was tiny but spotless, and the shared bathroom and shower were literally right outside my door (and never once occupied when I needed it). I was also rather giddy to discover that I had my very own gargoyle just outside the window. The only downside has been mentioned by others before me: THE STAIRS--I'll be seeing those stairs in my nightmares for years to come. But, hey, it's good exercise and it's the perfect justification to have another pannenkoeken with cream! 
